docs.description: TriStar Wellness Solutions, Inc., formerly Biopack Environmental Solutions Inc., is engaged in developing, marketing and selling, NCP's Beaute de Maman product lines, which is a line of skincare and other products specifically targeted for pregnant women, as well developing the Soft and Smooth Assets. The Company supplied its biodegradable food containers and industrial packaging products to multinational corporations, supermarket chains and restaurants located across North America, Europe and Asia. During the year ended December 31, 2011, the Company's product line-up of food containers and industrial packaging products includes plates, bowls, boxes, trays, shoe supporters and cases for electronic devices.

docs.name: Nippon Paper Industries Co., Ltd (3863)
docs.description: Nippon Paper Industries Co., Ltd. is a Japan-based paper manufacturing company. The Company operates in four business segments. The Paper and Pulp segment manufactures and sells western paper and pulp. The Paper-related segment manufactures and sells paper processed products, chemical products, adhesive products and paper containers. The Lumber, Construction Materials and Civil Engineering-related segment purchases and sells lumber and construction materials, manufactures and sells construction materials, as well as involves in the civil engineering business. The Others segment is engaged in the logistics, leisure and other businesses. As of March 31, 2012, the Company had 109 subsidiaries and 42 associated companies.
